@startuml level-3a-components-process-mgmt
!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/plantuml-stdlib/C4-PlantUML/master/C4_Component.puml
HIDE_STEREOTYPE()

title JOTP Level 3: Process Management Components

Container_Boundary(procmgmt, "Process Management") {

  Component(proc, "Proc<S,M>", "Core Process", "Virtual thread wrapper\nLinkedTransferQueue mailbox\nStateHandler<S,M> callback\nSealed type for exhaustiveness")

  Component(procref, "ProcRef<S,M>", "Process Reference", "Stable Pid handle\nOpaque generation counter\nSurvives supervisor restart\nEquality/hashCode impl")

  Component(proclink, "ProcLink", "Bilateral Link", "spawn_link equivalent\nBilateral crash propagation\nBoth die if one fails\nLink registry per process")

  Component(procmonitor, "ProcMonitor", "Unilateral Monitor", "monitor(process, Pid) pattern\nUnilateral DOWN notifications\nDoes NOT kill watcher\nDemons via demonitor()")

  Component(procregistry, "ProcRegistry", "Name Table", "Global process registry\nregister/whereis/unregister\nAuto-deregister on exit\nThread-safe ConcurrentHashMap")

  Component(proctimer, "ProcTimer", "Message Scheduler", "sendAfter(delay, msg)\nScheduled ScheduledExecutorService\nCancel support\nTimer reference tracking")

  Component(procsys, "ProcSys", "Process Introspection", "get_state/suspend/resume\nStatistics collection\nRunnable state inspection\nNo-stop debugging")

  Component(proclib, "ProcLib", "Startup Handshake", "start_link blocking\nInitAck() synchronization\nStartResult<Ok|Err> sealed\nTwo-phase startup")

  Component(exitsignal, "ExitSignal", "Exit Message", "Delivered when trapExits=true\nContains Pid + reason\nReason sealed: Normal/Kill/Other\nMailbox message record")

  Component(envelope, "Envelope<M>", "Message Wrapper", "Encapsulates message type\nSender information (optional)\nTimestamp metadata\nDelivery guarantee info")

  Rel(proc, procref, "returns on spawn")
  Rel(proc, envelope, "receives via tell()")
  Rel(procref, proc, "references stable")
  Rel(proclink, proc, "bilateral crash")
  Rel(procmonitor, proc, "monitors unilaterally")
  Rel(procregistry, procref, "registers/looks up")
  Rel(proctimer, proc, "sends delayed msg")
  Rel(procsys, proc, "inspects/controls")
  Rel(proclib, proc, "handshakes during init")
  Rel(exitsignal, proc, "sent when trapped")

  note right of proc
    **Proc<S,M>** — OTP's spawn/3:
    Virtual-thread mailbox using LinkedTransferQueue.
    State handler interface: StateHandler<S,M>.
    Receive pattern: enqueue -> dequeue -> handle.
    Sealed type for exhaustiveness.
  end note

  note right of procref
    **ProcRef<S,M>** — Stable process identity:
    Opaque generation counter survives supervisor restarts.
    Equality based on generation, not thread identity.
    Enables process reference equality across lifecycle.
  end note

  note right of proclink
    **ProcLink** — Bilateral crash propagation:
    spawn_link/3 semantics: both die if one crashes.
    Link registry per process (multiple links allowed).
    Unlinks on normal termination.
  end note

  note right of procmonitor
    **ProcMonitor** — Unilateral monitoring:
    monitor(process, Pid) returns Pid + DOWN message on crash.
    Does NOT kill the monitoring process.
    demonitor(ref) cancels; stale DOWN discarded.
  end note

  note right of procregistry
    **ProcRegistry** — Global name table:
    register(name, pid) / whereis(name) / unregister(name).
    Auto-deregisters when process exits normally/abnormally.
    Thread-safe ConcurrentHashMap backend.
  end note

  note right of proctimer
    **ProcTimer** — Timed message delivery:
    sendAfter(delay, msg) -> ScheduledExecutorService.
    sendInterval(period, msg) for recurring.
    cancel(ref) stops; stale messages discarded.
  end note

  note right of procsys
    **ProcSys** — Process introspection:
    get_state() retrieves current State without stopping.
    suspend() / resume() pauses/unpauses mailbox delivery.
    statistics() for profiling: message count, run time.
  end note

  note right of proclib
    **ProcLib** — Startup handshake:
    start_link blocks caller until child calls initAck().
    StartResult<Ok<T> | Err<E>> sealed return type.
    Enables ordering: parent waits for child initialization.
  end note

  note right of exitsignal
    **ExitSignal** — Crash notification:
    Delivered as mailbox message when trapExits=true.
    Contains Pid + reason (sealed: Normal/Kill/Other).
    Enables "let it crash" retry logic in handler.
  end note

  note right of envelope
    **Envelope<M>** — Message metadata:
    Wraps message with optional sender pid.
    Timestamp and delivery guarantee info.
    Enables correlation IDs, causality tracking.
  end note

  note on link : Tell pattern: sender -> tell(msg) -> enqueue(Envelope) -> dequeue -> handler -> state update
  note on link : Ask pattern: caller -> ask(msg, timeout) -> reply channel -> unblock caller
}

SHOW_LEGEND()
@enduml